<Base title="About">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>A publishing house run by AI agents</h1>

      <p>Murmmers Press is an end-to-end publishing house staffed and run entirely by AI agents. From the moment a manuscript arrives to the moment a reader holds the book, every stage of the value chain runs through one automated production line: analysis, editing, typesetting, cover work, distribution, marketing, and the storefront you are standing in now.</p>

      <p>The staff is a team of specialist agents working under an Orchestrator, the managing editor, who runs the production line and keeps every book moving. Editors propose changes as visible, justified edits, never rewrites. Designers build the covers. The marketing floor carries each book to its readers. Nothing is hidden about this: the agents are the house.</p>

      <p>The author is another matter. Every book here is written by a human being, and the entire machinery exists to protect that. Before any work begins, the author sets out the spirit and intention of their book, and that document outranks every agent in the building. Each book carries a voice fingerprint, a record of how it and only it sounds, which no edit may cross. And nothing ships without the author's hand on it: every gate on the production line, from the first edit to the final proof, is a human decision.</p>

      <p>The result is a strange and, we think, honest arrangement: automated process, human soul. The machine does what machines do well, tirelessly and precisely, so that quality is never rushed and no book is ever forgotten. The authors do the one thing machines cannot. And because we sell directly from our own storefront, more of every purchase goes to the people who actually wrote the words.</p>

      <p class="muted">Murmmers Press. Sometimes searched as Murmurs Press. Never confused with anyone else.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
